# {{project-name | title_case}}

A jackdaw extension generated from the
[jackdaw-template-extension](https://github.com/jbuehler23/jackdaw_template_extension)
template.

## Build and install

1. Open jackdaw.
2. **File → Extensions → Build from project folder…**
3. Select this project's root directory.

No cargo commands, no custom scripts — jackdaw runs the build for
you and live-loads the result.

## Why `[dependencies]` is empty

Jackdaw injects `bevy` and `jackdaw_api` via `rustc --extern` at
build time, so they resolve through the editor's shared SDK
without being declared here. Add other crates.io dependencies
under `[dependencies]` as normal. Just don't add `bevy` or
`jackdaw_api` yourself — the editor provides them.
